dvgrab: dvgrab (Digital Video Utility)
dvgrab:
dvgrab: dvgrab receives audio and video data from a digital camcorder via an 
dvgrab: IEEE 1394 (widely known as FireWire) link and stores them into an AVI 
dvgrab: file. It features autosplit of long video sequences into several files, 
dvgrab: and supports saving the data as raw frames, AVI type 1, AVI type 2, 
dvgrab: and image files.
